File Management
ls	List directory contents
cp	Copy files and directories
mv	Move or rename files
rm	Remove files or directories
mkdir	Create directories
rmdir	Remove empty directories
touch	Create empty file or update timestamps
find	Search for files in a directory hierarchy
ln	Create links between files
chmod	Change file permissions
chown	Change file owner and group
stat	Display file status
file	Determine file type
du	Estimate file space usage
df	Report file system disk space usage

Text Processing
cat	Concatenate and display files
less	View file contents page by page
more	View file contents one screen at a time
head	Output the first part of files
tail	Output the last part of files
grep	Search text using patterns
sed	Stream editor for filtering and transforming text
awk	Pattern scanning and processing language
sort	Sort lines of text files
uniq	Report or omit repeated lines
wc	Print newline, word, and byte counts
cut	Remove sections from each line of files
paste	Merge lines of files
tr	Translate or delete characters
diff	Compare files line by line
tee	Read from stdin and write to stdout and files

System Information
uname	Print system information
hostname	Show or set the system hostname
uptime	Show how long system has been running
whoami	Print current user name
who	Show who is logged on
w	Show who is logged on and what they are doing
id	Print user and group information
date	Display or set the date and time
cal	Display a calendar
top	Display system processes and resource usage
ps	Report a snapshot of current processes
kill	Send a signal to a process
env	Display environment variables
printenv	Print all or part of environment

Networking
ping	Send ICMP echo request to network hosts
curl	Transfer data from or to a server
nc	Read and write network connections
ssh	Secure shell remote login
scp	Secure copy files between hosts
sftp	Secure file transfer program
netstat	Network statistics
ifconfig	Configure network interfaces
traceroute	Trace the route to a network host
dig	DNS lookup utility
nslookup	Query Internet name servers
host	DNS lookup utility

Compression and Archives
tar	Archive files
gzip	Compress files
gunzip	Decompress files
zip	Package and compress files
unzip	Extract compressed files
bzip2	Block-sorting file compressor
xz	Compress files using LZMA

Searching and Finding
find	Search for files in directory hierarchy
locate	Find files by name quickly
which	Locate a command
whereis	Locate the binary, source, and manual page for a command
type	Describe a command

Disk and Storage
df	Report file system disk space usage
du	Estimate file space usage
mount	Mount a file system
umount	Unmount a file system
fdisk	Partition table manipulator (Linux)
diskutil	Disk utility (macOS)

User and Permissions
passwd	Change user password
su	Switch user
sudo	Execute a command as another user
chmod	Change file mode bits
chown	Change file owner and group
chgrp	Change group ownership
groups	Print group memberships
finger	User information lookup
last	Show listing of last logged in users

Process Management
ps	Report current processes
top	Display and manage processes
wait	Wait for process to complete
kill	Send signal to a process
killall	Kill processes by name
bg	Resume suspended job in background
fg	Bring job to foreground
jobs	List active jobs
nohup	Run a command immune to hangups
nice	Run a command with modified scheduling priority

Shell and Scripting
echo	Display a line of text
printf	Format and print data
read	Read a line from standard input
test	Evaluate conditional expression
expr	Evaluate expressions
xargs	Build and execute commands from standard input
alias	Create command shortcuts
history	Display command history
source	Execute commands from a file in current shell
export	Set environment variables

Version Control
git	Distributed version control system
diff	Compare files line by line
patch	Apply a diff file to an original

